  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Esther Sturge comments on the charge that John Quincy Adams is not an abolitionist. Sturge believes that &quot;he is evidently a friend to freedom.&quot; She criticizes William Lloyd Garrison for his involvement in such a large number of causes. Sturge writes to Maria Weston Chapman: &quot;Unity of purpose will always carry a point even if there are a variety of shades, &amp; I would not rebuke any who are not entirely with you, less I should make them my enemies, ...&quot; Sturge quotes Thomas Clarkson&apos;s praise of Zachary Macaulay.</subfield>
